
                                            A mother and her five children died in the shack fire on Monday. 
                                         CAPE TOWN - The Cooperative Governance and Traditional Affairs Minister says his department and other government entities are doing everything to assist after a family was killed in a fire in Phola Park, in Philippi East. A mother and her five children died in the shack fire on Monday. Minister Des van Rooyen visited the family of the deceased earlier on Wednesday. “And we have roped in our social development services to provide counselling services.”